Child of the Temple		KEY:Child of the Temple ~ Trait		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.FaithTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Child of the Temple ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.FaithTrait]		DESC:You have long served at a temple in a city, and not only did you pick up on many of the nobility's customs, you spent much time in the temple libraries studying your faith.																			STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NUMCHOICES=1|SKILLSNAMED|Knowledge (Nobility)|Knowledge (Religion)							BONUS:SKILL|Knowledge (Nobility),Knowledge (Religion)|1|TYPE=Trait								CSKILL:LIST		SOURCEPAGE:p.328	BENEFIT:You have long served at a temple in a city, and not only did you pick up on many of the nobility's customs, you spent much time in the temple libraries studying your faith. You gain a +1 trait bonus on Knowledge (Nobility) and Knowledge (Religion) checks, and %1 is always a class skill for you.|%LIST
Devotee of the Green		KEY:Devotee of the Green ~ Trait		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.FaithTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Devotee of the Green ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.FaithTrait]		DESC:Your faith in the natural world or one of the gods of nature makes it easy for you to pick up on related concepts.																													STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NUMCHOICES=1|SKILLSNAMED|Knowledge (Geography)|Knowledge (Nature)							BONUS:SKILL|Knowledge (Geography),Knowledge (Nature)|1|TYPE=Trait									CSKILL:LIST		SOURCEPAGE:p.328	BENEFIT:Your faith in the natural world or one of the gods of nature makes it easy for you to pick up on related concepts. You gain a +1 trait bonus on Knowledge (Geography) and Knowledge (Nature) checks, and %1 is always a class skill for you.|%LIST
Ease of Faith			KEY:Ease of Faith ~ Trait			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.FaithTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Ease of Faith ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.FaithTrait]			DESC:Your mentor, the person who invested your faith in you from an early age, took steps to ensure that you understood that what powers your divine magic is no different than that which powers the magic of other religions.																																		BONUS:SKILL|Diplomacy|1|TYPE=Trait														CSKILL:Diplomacy	SOURCEPAGE:p.328	BENEFIT:Your mentor, the person who invested your faith in you from an early age, took steps to ensure that you understood that what powers your divine magic is no different than that which powers the magic of other religions. You gain a +1 trait bonus on Diplomacy checks, and Diplomacy is always a class skill for you.
History of Heresy			KEY:History of Heresy ~ Trait			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.FaithTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,History of Heresy ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.FaithTrait]		DESC:You were raised with heretical views that have made it not only difficult for you to accept most religious beliefs, but you also have had to live with the fact that you or those you love were often treated as pariahs.																																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.328	BENEFIT:You were raised with heretical views that have made it not only difficult for you to accept most religious beliefs, but you also have had to live with the fact that you or those you love were often treated as pariahs. As long as you do not possess any levels in a class that grants divine spellcasting power, you gain a +1 trait bonus on all saving throws made against divine spells.
Indomitable Faith			KEY:Indomitable Faith ~ Trait			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.FaithTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Indomitable Faith ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.FaithTrait]		DESC:You were born in a region where your faith was not popular, yet you never abandoned it.																																																		BONUS:CHECKS|Will|1|TYPE=Trait																							SOURCEPAGE:p.328	BENEFIT:You were born in a region where your faith was not popular, yet you never abandoned it. You gain a +1 trait bonus on Will saves as a result.
Sacred Conduit			KEY:Sacred Conduit ~ Trait			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.FaithTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Sacred Conduit ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.FaithTrait]			DESC:Your birth was particularly painful and difficult for your mother, who needed potent divine magic to ensure you survived; your mother may or may not have survived. In any event, the magic infused you from an early age, and you now channel divine energy with greater ease than most.																																				BONUS:VAR|ChannelEnergyDC|1|TYPE=Trait				SOURCEPAGE:p.329	BENEFIT:Your birth was particularly painful and difficult for your mother, who needed potent divine magic to ensure you survived; your mother may or may not have survived. In any event, the magic infused you from an early age, and you now channel divine energy with greater ease than most. Whenever you channel energy, you gain a +1 trait bonus to the save DC of your channeled energy.
Sacred Touch			KEY:Sacred Touch ~ Trait			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.FaithTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Sacred Touch ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.FaithTrait]			DESC:You were exposed to a potent source of positive energy as a child, perhaps by being born under the right cosmic sign, or maybe because one of your parents was a gifted healer.																																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.329	BENEFIT:You were exposed to a potent source of positive energy as a child, perhaps by being born under the right cosmic sign, or maybe because one of your parents was a gifted healer. As a standard action, you may automatically stabilize a dying creature merely by touching it.
Scholar of the Great Beyond	KEY:Scholar of the Great Beyond ~ Trait	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.FaithTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Scholar of the Great Beyond ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.FaithTrait]	DESC:Your great interests as a child did not lie with current events or the mundane-- you have always felt out of place, as if you were born in the wrong era.																						STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NUMCHOICES=1|SKILLSNAMED|Knowledge (History)|Knowledge (Planes)								BONUS:SKILL|Knowledge (History),Knowledge (Planes)|1|TYPE=Trait									CSKILL:LIST		SOURCEPAGE:p.329	BENEFIT:Your great interests as a child did not lie with current events or the mundane-- you have always felt out of place, as if you were born in the wrong era. You gain a +1 trait bonus on Knowledge (History) and Knowledge (Planes) checks, and %1 is always a class skill for you.|%LIST

